		<div class="container">
			<div class="card">
				<div class="card-body">
					<div class="row mb-4 mt-3">
						<div class="col-lg-6">
							<h2>Friendship Lights</h2>
							<p>
								These lights are a matched pair which were made for a friend who wanted to stay connected to someone who was moving away (both their names begin with the letter K).
							</p>
							<p>
								When you press the button on one, the other lights up to let your friend know you're thinking about them.
							</p>						
						</div>
						<div class="col-lg-6">
							<img class="rounded img-fluid" src="../assets/imgs/friendship-lights1.jpg">
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="row">
						<div class="col-lg-6 mb-4 order-2 order-lg-1">
							<img class="rounded img-fluid" src="../assets/imgs/friendship-lights2.jpg">
						</div>
						<div class="col-lg-6 mb-4 order-1 order-lg-2">
							<p>
								I made them using a pair of Adafruit Feather HUZZAH's with ESP8266. They use WiFi to connect over the internet through IFTTT.
							</p>
							<p>
								The case was made of layers of lasercut MDF glued together and topped with etched acrylic to give a diffuse glow to the LEDs inside.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

